{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse was sick...{\r}

612
01:02:28,393 --> 01:02:32,853
…感冒，疼痛，肺淤血
{\fscx70\fscy70}...with rheums, and aches
and lung congestions.{\r}

613
01:02:33,732 --> 01:02:37,031
失眠使他眼窩嚴重發黑
{\fscx70\fscy70}Insomnia stained
his eye sockets like soot.{\r}

614
01:02:37,869 --> 01:02:40,861
他從雞那纏繞的腸道中…
{\fscx70\fscy70}He read auguries in
the snarled intestines of chickens...{\r}

615
01:02:42,073 --> 01:02:45,634
…或者是貓毛在風中飄散的方向中
占卜未來
{\fscx70\fscy70}...or the blow of cat hair
released to the wind.{\r}

616
01:02:46,444 --> 01:02:51,404
得到的都是兇兆，這讓他感覺身陷囹圄
{\fscx70\fscy70}And the omens promised bad luck,
which moated and dungeoned him.{\r}

617
01:03:33,124 --> 01:03:35,684
為什麼這些活都是你幹？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How come it's you
that's gotta do all the chores?{\r}

618
01:03:35,860 --> 01:03:40,092
查理和鮑勃多給了些錢給瑪莎
所以他們就不用做
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley and Bob pay extry to Martha
so that they don't have to.{\r}

619
01:03:41,399 --> 01:03:43,458
但還是不公平
{\fscx70\fscy70}It still don't seem fair.{\r}

620
01:03:50,241 --> 01:03:51,765
瑪莎
{\fscx70\fscy70}Martha.{\r}

621
01:03:53,511 --> 01:03:56,105
噢，看看誰來了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, look what the cat dragged in.{\r}

622
01:04:00,919 --> 01:04:02,181
你從肯塔基來的？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You come from Kentucky?{\r}

623
01:04:05,590 --> 01:04:09,424
你怎麼兩耳不聞窗外事，瑪莎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why do you have your head in a hole,
Martha?{\r}

624
01:04:12,464 --> 01:04:16,195
伍德和迪克幾個月前有過槍戰
{\fscx70\fscy70}Wood and Dick had a shooting scrape
a few months ago.{\r}

625
01:04:17,769 --> 01:04:19,031
去看著水壺，愛達
{\fscx70\fscy70}Cover the kettle, Ida.{\r}

626
01:04:24,309 --> 01:04:26,607
你和迪克為什麼那樣？
{\fscx70\fscy70}And what did you and Dick
get in a scrape about?{\r}

627
01:04:30,482 --> 01:04:34,475
我爸爸的老婆在煎豬排的時候…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, he tampered
with my daddy's wife...{\r}

628
01:04:34,652 --> 01:04:38,019
…他卻來和她調情…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...while a pork chop
burned on the skillet...{\r}

629
01:04:38,189 --> 01:04:39,713
…所以我向他開槍
{\fscx70\fscy70}...so I shot at him.{\r}

630
01:04:44,796 --> 01:04:49,199
愛達！
撇油脂的時候不要把大拇指伸進去！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Ida! Do not stick your thumb
in the cream when you skim it.{\r}

631
01:04:50,368 --> 01:04:55,567
他的狡詐和沾花惹草的作風…
{\fscx70\fscy70}His chicanery and his philandering ways...{\r}

632
01:04:55,740 --> 01:04:57,708
…是我們之間怨恨的導火索
{\fscx70\fscy70}...has instigated such malice.{\r}

633
01:04:57,876 --> 01:05:01,812
他就像草叢中的黃蛇一樣不可靠，瑪莎
{\fscx70\fscy70}He's a yellow snake in the grass
and he can't be trusted, Martha.{\r}

634
01:05:04,716 --> 01:05:08,083
但這事迪克的說法和你完全不同
{\fscx70\fscy70}Dick told me a complete other version
of that affray.{\r}

635
01:05:09,554 --> 01:05:12,216
伍德·海特在樓下
{\fscx70\fscy70}Wood Hite's downstairs.{\r}

636
01:05:12,924 --> 01:05:14,619
你說他來這兒了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You mean he's here?{\r}

637
01:05:17,395 --> 01:05:20,091
對，他昨晚很晚來的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, he come in late last night.{\r}

638
01:05:23,802 --> 01:05:24,826
嗨，冷靜點！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hey, simmer down!{\r}

639
01:05:25,003 --> 01:05:29,565
別上去惹事了，孩子們！早飯馬上就好了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't get into a fracas up there, you boys!
I've got breakfast almost ready.{\r}

640
01:07:40,471 --> 01:07:42,666
他還在吸氣
{\fscx70\fscy70}He's still sucking air.{\r}

641
01:07:43,841 --> 01:07:46,036
但我想他應該掛了
{\fscx70\fscy70}But I think he's a goner.{\r}

642
01:07:56,187 --> 01:07:59,486
也許你們該上來祝他黃泉路上走好
{\fscx70\fscy70}Maybe y'all better come wish him well
on his journey.{\r}

643
01:08:26,284 --> 01:08:27,751
伍德？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Wood?{\r}

644
01:08:30,188 --> 01:08:32,452
你是個好夥計，伍德
{\fscx70\fscy70}You were a good fellow, Wood.{\r}

645
01:08:32,690 --> 01:08:36,182
哦，希望你沒受太多苦，伍德
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, I sure hope you're not
in frightful pain, Wood.{\r}

646
01:08:36,761 --> 01:08:40,492
我想給你點水喝，但我怕你會噎著
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'd get you something to drink,
but I'm afraid you'd just choke on it.{\r}

647
01:08:41,866 --> 01:08:44,027
小愛達會想你的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Little Ida's gonna miss you.{\r}

648
01:08:44,202 --> 01:08:46,329
家裡其他人也會的
{\fscx70\fscy70}So is the rest of the family.{\r}

649
01:08:49,540 --> 01:08:53,169
嗯，這事算解決了
不過不能把他帶到裡士滿去
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, one thing's settled.
Can't take him into Richmond.{\r}

650
01:08:54,245 --> 01:08:55,303
為什麼？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why not?{\r}

651
01:08:56,781 --> 01:08:59,341
這個，一來，警察會把鮑勃抓進去
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, one, sheriff'll put Bob in jail.{\r}

652
01:08:59,517 --> 01:09:03,385
二來，要是傑西發現
他的表弟被殺死在我們這裡…
{\fscx70\fscy70}And two, Jesse'll find out his cousin
Wood's been shot in our house...{\r}

653
01:09:03,554 --> 01:09:06,955
…那我們就都完了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and then that'll be the end
of each and every one of us.{\r}

654
01:09:16,868 --> 01:09:20,531
「冷酷而又殘暴得插了進來…
{\fscx70\fscy70}"And in one merciless, violent thrust
broke in...{\r}

655
01:09:20,972 --> 01:09:23,805
…伴隨著香水和啤酒…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and carried all before him,
and scented and brewed...{\r}

656
01:09:23,975 --> 01:09:26,500
…還有我處子之血的味道…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...reeking with blood of my virginity...{\r}

657
01:09:26,677 --> 01:09:31,205
…在我的身體內膨脹到了極致」
{\fscx70\fscy70}...up to its utmost length in my body."{\r}

658
01:09:32,817 --> 01:09:35,684
他並沒有消失，讓你失望了
{\fscx70\fscy70}He ain't disappeared,
if that's what you were hoping.{\r}

659
01:09:40,158 --> 01:09:42,126
你在讀哪一章？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What chapter you on?{\r}

660
01:09:42,627 --> 01:09:47,655
她在直布羅陀遇到了一些阿爾及利亞海盜
{\fscx70\fscy70}She's met some Algerian corsair
down at Gibraltar.{\r}

661
01:09:47,832 --> 01:09:50,130
這讓她很興奮
{\fscx70\fscy70}Got herself all agitated.{\r}

662
01:09:52,470 --> 01:09:53,903
腿怎樣了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How's that leg?{\r}

663
01:09:54,705 --> 01:09:58,869
痛得要死，鮑勃，謝謝你的關心
{\fscx70\fscy70}Full of torment, Bob. Thanks for asking.{\r}

664
01:10:44,755 --> 01:10:47,417
虛心的人有福了…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Blessed are the poor in spirit...{\r}

665
01:10:47,592 --> 01:10:49,856
…因為天國是他們的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.{\r}

666
01:10:51,295 --> 01:10:56,858
哀慟的人有福了，因為他們必得安慰
{\fscx70\fscy70}Blessed are them that mourn,
for they shall be comforted.{\r}

667
01:10:59,003 --> 01:11:00,937
…的人有福了…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Blessed are the...{\r}

668
01:11:04,475 --> 01:11:05,999
溫柔
{\fscx70\fscy70}Meek.{\r}

669
01:11:08,279 --> 01:11:10,110
溫柔的人有福了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Blessed are the meek.{\r}

670
01:11:46,083 --> 01:11:48,142
- 是他嗎？
- 是的
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Is it him?
- Yeah.{\r}

671
01:11:48,319 --> 01:11:51,345
他來這兒幹嘛？
你覺得他知道伍德的事情嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why is he here? Does he know
about Wood, do you think?{\r}

672
01:11:51,522 --> 01:11:53,922
我不清楚，我只知道他不是很想念他
{\fscx70\fscy70}I don't know. All I know is
he don't miss very much.{\r}

673
01:11:54,091 --> 01:11:58,050
- 如果他問到你，我該怎麼回答？
- 告訴他我和馬蒂在堪薩斯城
{\fscx70\fscy70}- What should I say about you if he asks?
- Tell him I'm in K.C. With Mattie.{\r}

674
01:12:00,765 --> 01:12:04,565
他在獵殺野牛
能見到你們他真的很高興
{\fscx70\fscy70}He was buffalo hunting.
He was thrilled to meet yours truly.{\r}

675
01:12:04,735 --> 01:12:08,671
是啊，在歐洲，有兩個美國人
人們肯定認得…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, over there in Europe there's only
two Americans they know for certain...{\r}

676
01:12:08,839 --> 01:12:11,774
…馬克·吐溫和傑西·詹姆斯…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...Mark Twain and Jesse James.{\r}

677
01:12:13,144 --> 01:12:16,375
- 怎麼，是這個孩子
- 一切還好嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Why, it's the kid.
- How's everything?{\r}

678
01:12:18,816 --> 01:12:21,410
- 我從不摘下槍
- 是嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}- I never take off my gun belts.
- Yeah?{\r}

679
01:12:21,586 --> 01:12:23,144
好主意
{\fscx70\fscy70}Good thinking.{\r}

680
01:12:29,260 --> 01:12:31,524
噢，查理，你腳受傷了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, Charley, did you hurt your leg?{\r}

681
01:12:34,065 --> 01:12:36,090
是啊，我滑…我從屋頂滑下去了…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, I slipped...
I slipped off the roof...{\r}

682
01:12:36,267 --> 01:12:39,862
…像個傻子一樣摔在了雪地上
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I smacked down into a snow bank
like a ton of stupidness.{\r}

683
01:12:40,037 --> 01:12:42,699
前一秒我還在驚叫，「噢，天哪」
{\fscx70\fscy70}One second I'm screaming,
"Whoa, Nelly!"{\r}

684
01:12:42,873 --> 01:12:45,535
後一秒我已經被埋在齊脖深的雪地裡了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Next second, poof,
I'm neck-deep in snow.{\r}

685
01:12:48,446 --> 01:12:52,280
那麼，是什麼讓你在大冬天爬上屋頂的？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, whatever possessed you
to climb a roof in December?{\r}

686
01:12:58,289 --> 01:13:01,747
有一個…風箏
我說啥來著？有一隻貓
{\fscx70\fscy70}There was a k... A kite. What am I saying?
There was a cat.{\r}

687
01:13:01,926 --> 01:13:04,326
一隻貓，在屋頂上，我去追它
{\fscx70\fscy70}A cat. It was on the roof
and I went after him.{\r}

688
01:13:04,527 --> 01:13:09,055
是只公貓，在嗷嗷叫，我就摔了
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was a tomcat yowling
and what all, and I slipped.{\r}

689
01:13:21,010 --> 01:13:24,104
我以為你畸形腿了呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}I thought maybe your club foot
was gaining on you.{\r}

690
01:13:33,156 --> 01:13:34,783
是啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, yeah.{\r}

691
01:13:35,558 --> 01:13:39,790
迪克去堪薩斯見他老婆去了
他之前在這呆過一陣子
{\fscx70\fscy70}Dick went to Kansas City to be
with his wife. He was here for a bit.{\r}

692
01:13:59,415 --> 01:14:02,316
對了傑西，給你講個可愛的故事吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hey, here's a cute story, Jess.{\r}

693
01:14:02,485 --> 01:14:05,852
鮑勃11還是12歲的時候
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bobby was what, 11 or 12...{\r}

694
01:14:06,022 --> 01:14:09,185
非常非常仰慕你
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and you were by far
his most admired personage.{\r}

695
01:14:09,692 --> 01:14:10,852
不停地講你
{\fscx70\fscy70}He couldn't get enough.{\r}

696
01:14:11,027 --> 01:14:15,225
「傑西這樣」、「傑西那樣」
一天到晚說不倦
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was "Jesse this" and "Jesse that"
and "Jesse this" from sunrise to sunset.{\r}

697
01:14:15,398 --> 01:14:16,524
真有趣
{\fscx70\fscy70}Fascinating.{\r}

698
01:14:16,699 --> 01:14:18,428
還有更逗的呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}No, there's more. This is cute.{\r}

699
01:14:18,601 --> 01:14:23,368
有次我們在吃飯，鮑勃問
「你們知道傑西穿幾號鞋嗎？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}We're at supper and Bob asks,
"You know what size boot Jesse wears?"{\r}

700
01:14:23,539 --> 01:14:27,270
- 查理，傑西不想聽這個
- 鮑勃別插嘴，讓我說嘛
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Charley, Jesse doesn't wanna hear this.
- Shush, now, Bob, let me tell it.{\r}

701
01:14:27,443 --> 01:14:30,469
鮑勃說，「你知道傑西穿幾號鞋嗎？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob says... He says, "You know
what size boot Jesse wears?"{\r}

702
01:14:30,646 --> 01:14:33,809
他說，「6寸半」，還說，「這夠大嗎？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}He says, "Six and a half." He says,
"Ain't that a big enough boot...{\r}

703
01:14:33,983 --> 01:14:35,780
「他五尺八寸高呢」
{\fscx70\fscy70}...for a man 5'8"tall?"{\r}

704
01:14:35,952 --> 01:14:39,786
我就想逗逗他，他是我小弟弟嘛
{\fscx70\fscy70}I decided to josh him a little, you know,
he being my kid brother and everything.{\r}

705
01:14:39,956 --> 01:14:43,050
我就說，「因為他沒有腳指頭啊"
{\fscx70\fscy70}So I said, "He doesn't have toes is why."{\r}

706
01:14:43,226 --> 01:14:44,750
這故事太傻了啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's a really stupid story.{\r}

707
01:14:44,927 --> 01:14:49,523
「他有一次腳泡在水溝裡，
趾頭被鯰魚啃沒了」
{\fscx70\fscy70}"He was dangling his feet off a culvert
and a catfish nibbled his toes off."{\r}

708
01:14:49,699 --> 01:14:52,429
鮑勃想破了頭，就是想不明白
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob taxed himself trying to picture it.{\r}

709
01:14:59,308 --> 01:15:01,970
如果你覺得這故事好笑的話，
倒是個好笑話
{\fscx70\fscy70}That'd be a good joke if it was funny.{\r}

710
01:15:02,812 --> 01:15:05,337
很逗吧，傑西？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Isn't that a cute story, Jess?{\r}

711
01:15:15,224 --> 01:15:18,091
多給我講講吧，鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Give me some more conversations, Bob.{\r}

712
01:15:23,166 --> 01:15:28,331
我想到了一個更牛的，是關於你…
{\fscx70\fscy70}I got one. This one's about as crackerjack...
It's the one about your...{\r}

713
01:15:28,504 --> 01:15:30,404
讓鮑勃講吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}Let Bob tell it.{\r}

714
01:15:31,774 --> 01:15:33,571
好吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}All right.{\r}

715
01:15:40,116 --> 01:15:42,107
我都不知道你說什麼
{\fscx70\fscy70}I don't even know
what you're talking about.{\r}

716
01:15:42,285 --> 01:15:46,278
你不是說你和傑西有很多共同點嘛
{\fscx70\fscy70}About how you and Jesse
have so much in common.{\r}

717
01:15:49,325 --> 01:15:50,986
來講講吧，鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Go on, Bob.{\r}

718
01:15:51,160 --> 01:15:53,128
對啊，快，鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, come on, Bob.{\r}

719
01:15:53,863 --> 01:15:56,127
給我們講個故事
{\fscx70\fscy70}Tell us a story.{\r}

720
01:15:58,067 --> 01:16:02,663
- 不要
- 快啦，讓傑西高興一下
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Nope. No.
- Come on, entertain Jesse. He's here.{\r}

721
01:16:09,612 --> 01:16:11,136
說嘛
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on.{\r}

722
01:16:18,020 --> 01:16:21,922
說了你不要生氣，我覺得
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, if you'll pardon my saying so,
I guess...{\r}

723
01:16:22,091 --> 01:16:26,152
我們倆有很多重疊的地方，挺有趣的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...it is interesting the many ways
you and I overlap and whatnot.{\r}

724
01:16:27,463 --> 01:16:30,227
從我們的爸爸說起吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}I mean, you begin with our daddies.{\r}

725
01:16:30,399 --> 01:16:33,368
你爸爸是個浸信會牧師
{\fscx70\fscy70}Your daddy was a pastor
at the New Hope Baptist Church...{\r}

726
01:16:33,536 --> 01:16:38,269
而我爸爸是艾克塞爾西奧泉市的牧師
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and my daddy was a pastor
at the church in Excelsior Springs.{\r}

727
01:16:39,709 --> 01:16:44,043
你是家裡三個兄弟中最小的
我家五兄弟，我最小
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're the youngest of three James boys,
and I'm the youngest of five Ford boys.{\r}

728
01:16:45,848 --> 01:16:48,510
查理和我中間還有一個哥哥，韋伯
{\fscx70\fscy70}Between Charley and me,
there's another brother, Wilbur...{\r}

729
01:16:48,684 --> 01:16:50,709
他的名字是六個字母的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...with six letters in his name.{\r}

730
01:16:51,053 --> 01:16:56,650
你和弗蘭克中間有個哥哥叫羅伯特
名字也是六個字母的
{\fscx70\fscy70}And between Frank and you, is another
brother Robert, also with six letters.{\r}

731
01:16:56,859 --> 01:17:00,590
恰好我的洗禮教名也是羅伯特
{\fscx70\fscy70}And my Christian name
is Robert, of course.{\r}

732
01:17:01,931 --> 01:17:04,092
你眼睛是藍的，我也是
{\fscx70\fscy70}You have blue eyes, I have blue eyes.{\r}

733
01:17:04,267 --> 01:17:08,260
你五尺八寸高，我也是
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're 5'8"tall, I'm 5'8" tall.{\r}

734
01:17:13,009 --> 01:17:18,379
我12歲的時候列出來一長串的相似點
比你睡衣還長呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}Me, I must have had a list as long as
your nightshirt when I was 12, but...{\r}

735
01:17:18,548 --> 01:17:21,984
但是長大後這種好奇心了就沒了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...I seem to have lost some curiosities
over the years.{\r}

736
01:17:40,271 --> 01:17:42,466
他還真厲害
{\fscx70\fscy70}Ain't he something?{\r}

737
01:17:55,052 --> 01:17:59,250
我有沒有給你們講過
有個叫喬治·謝坡德的傢伙
{\fscx70\fscy70}Did I ever tell you the story about
that scalawag, George Shepherd?{\r}

738
01:17:59,557 --> 01:18:01,457
他是考崔爾（內戰時南方聯盟游擊隊指揮官）
底下的一個官兵
{\fscx70\fscy70}Shepherd's one of
Quantrill's lieutenants.{\r}

739
01:18:01,625 --> 01:18:04,321
我想起他是因為
他的故事和鮑勃有點像
{\fscx70\fscy70}He give me a story much like Bob's
what bring him to mind.{\r}

740
01:18:04,795 --> 01:18:07,320
他給我講
我們倆有多少多少相似點
{\fscx70\fscy70}Going on about how much
we had in common, and so on...{\r}

741
01:18:07,498 --> 01:18:10,023
就想加入我們
{\fscx70\fscy70}...so he could get in the gang.{\r}

742
01:18:10,201 --> 01:18:13,329
沒想到他對我心懷怨恨
{\fscx70\fscy70}How could I have known
he had a grudge against me?{\r}

743
01:18:13,504 --> 01:18:17,998
沒想到他為了贏得我歡心，謊話連篇
{\fscx70\fscy70}How could I have known
he was lying to get on my good side?{\r}

744
01:18:18,175 --> 01:18:23,169
我說，"喬治，加入我們吧，很高興你入伙」
{\fscx70\fscy70}I said, "George, come on aboard.
Glad to have you."{\r}

745
01:18:23,347 --> 01:18:28,148
喬治以為自己很聰明，但其實不然
{\fscx70\fscy70}George thought he was smart,
except he wasn't.{\r}

746
01:18:29,086 --> 01:18:32,214
有天早上，喬治進來營地
{\fscx70\fscy70}One morning, George rides into camp...{\r}

747
01:18:32,389 --> 01:18:34,584
就有二十來支槍指著他
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and about 20 guns open up on him.{\r}

748
01:18:38,395 --> 01:18:42,855
喬治只有一隻眼，
要陰傑西，得有兩隻眼
{\fscx70\fscy70}See, old George, he only had one eye. You
gotta have two eyes, you wanna get Jesse.{\r}

749
01:18:47,705 --> 01:18:50,833
你不應該把我和喬治·謝坡德相提並論
{\fscx70\fscy70}You ought not think of me
like you do George Shepherd.{\r}

750
01:18:52,176 --> 01:18:54,406
你讓我想起了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}You brought him to mind.{\r}

751
01:18:55,346 --> 01:18:57,644
這不是什麼抬舉我的話
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, it's not very flattering.{\r}

752
01:19:03,621 --> 01:19:06,419
飯做得真好吃，瑪莎
{\fscx70\fscy70}Sure is good eating, Martha.{\r}

753
01:19:07,291 --> 01:19:09,521
你喜歡就好
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I'm so glad you enjoyed it.{\r}

754
01:19:09,693 --> 01:19:11,854
喬治為什麼會對你心懷怨恨？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How come George
had a grudge against you?{\r}

755
01:19:16,767 --> 01:19:20,863
我問你呢，喬治為什麼會對你心懷怨恨？
{\fscx70\fscy70}I said, how come George
had a grudge against you?{\r}

756
01:19:26,577 --> 01:19:31,310
喬治有個侄子
他想讓我在內戰時，保護他侄子
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you see, George had a nephew
he wanted me to protect during the war.{\r}

757
01:19:31,482 --> 01:19:33,712
那人身上有5000美元
{\fscx70\fscy70}This nephew had 5000 dollars on him.{\r}

758
01:19:33,884 --> 01:19:38,480
結果他被殺了，錢也被搶光
{\fscx70\fscy70}It just so happens he winds up killed
and someone swipes that money.{\r}

759
01:19:38,656 --> 01:19:42,524
喬治蹲監獄的時候，有人偷偷告訴他
{\fscx70\fscy70}And when George is in prison,
someone whispers to him:{\r}

760
01:19:42,693 --> 01:19:46,424
「是傑西·詹姆斯殺了那孩子的"
{\fscx70\fscy70}"It was Jesse James
slit the boy's throat."{\r}

761
01:19:51,168 --> 01:19:53,636
只是些流言蜚語，是吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was just mean gossip, was it?{\r}

762
01:19:55,439 --> 01:19:58,738
鮑勃是這方面的專家，
我們請教他吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob's the expert. Let's put it to him.{\r}

763
01:20:03,814 --> 01:20:06,214
哦，天啊，我惹惱他了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, dear, I made him cranky.{\r}

764
01:20:06,383 --> 01:20:10,183
我沒有生氣，只是以前我經歷過這種事
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm not cranky. I just been
through this before is all.{\r}

765
01:20:10,354 --> 01:20:13,517
周圍的人都嘲笑我，沒完沒了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Most people get around on making fun
of me. They don't ever let up.{\r}

766
01:20:13,691 --> 01:20:15,750
某人真夠怕羞的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Someone's getting awful fresh over there.{\r}

767
01:20:15,926 --> 01:20:18,622
女人，閉嘴行嗎
{\fscx70\fscy70}Woman, shut your face for once.{\r}

768
01:20:25,636 --> 01:20:27,968
我不想你溜回房間生悶氣
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't want you to skip off
to your room and pout...{\r}

769
01:20:28,138 --> 01:20:30,663
你還不知道我為什麼過來這邊
{\fscx70\fscy70}...without knowing why I come by
for this visit.{\r}

770
01:20:31,475 --> 01:20:33,705
為什麼？想給我們道歉
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why? So you could
tell us how sorry you are...{\r}

771
01:20:33,877 --> 01:20:36,437
因為你揍了我們的堂弟艾伯特一頓？
{\fscx70\fscy70}...you had to slap our cousin Albert around?{\r}

772
01:20:50,060 --> 01:20:51,891
我過來
{\fscx70\fscy70}I come by...{\r}

773
01:20:52,062 --> 01:20:55,463
是想問你們兩兄弟
{\fscx70\fscy70}...to ask if one of you two Fords...{\r}

774
01:20:55,666 --> 01:20:59,033
想不想和我一起上路
{\fscx70\fscy70}...would care to ride with me
in a journey or two.{\r}

775
01:20:59,436 --> 01:21:02,803
我看我們都覺得應該選查理吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}I guess we both agree
it ought to be Charley.{\r}

776
01:21:02,973 --> 01:21:05,771
你太急躁了點
{\fscx70\fscy70}You've been acting sort of testy.{\r}

777
01:21:36,740 --> 01:21:38,970
你最近有沒有見過伍德·海特？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Have you seen Wood Hite lately?{\r}

778
01:21:39,476 --> 01:21:43,003
沒有
{\fscx70\fscy70}No. Not at all.{\r}

779
01:21:50,988 --> 01:21:53,650
這燉菜裡肯定加了松鼠肉
{\fscx70\fscy70}I swear that stew
had some squirrel meat in it.{\r}

780
01:21:53,824 --> 01:21:56,520
- 還在和他吵？
- 對
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Still arguing with you, is it?
- Yeah.{\r}

781
01:21:57,294 --> 01:21:59,228
- 你是查爾斯·福特？
- 是的，太太
{\fscx70\fscy70}- You're Charles Ford?
- Yes, ma'am.{\r}

782
01:21:59,396 --> 01:22:01,455
我們以前見過
{\fscx70\fscy70}You've seen me once or twice before.{\r}

783
01:22:02,800 --> 01:22:04,734
我有封喬治·海特寄來的信
{\fscx70\fscy70}I got a letter from George Hite.{\r}

784
01:22:05,369 --> 01:22:08,270
他找不到他兒子了
{\fscx70\fscy70}He hasn't seen hide nor hair of him.{\r}

785
01:22:09,773 --> 01:22:11,968
你說你沒見過伍德？
{\fscx70\fscy70}And you say you haven't seen Wood?{\r}

786
01:22:12,710 --> 01:22:15,873
我想不出來他能去哪
{\fscx70\fscy70}No, l... I can't imagine where he could be.{\r}

787
01:22:43,274 --> 01:22:44,298
是嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah?{\r}

788
01:22:45,476 --> 01:22:47,637
睡夠了沒？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You finished with your sleeping?{\r}

789
01:22:49,146 --> 01:22:51,671
如果沒什麼事的話，我想多睡幾個小時
{\fscx70\fscy70}I could use a couple more hours
if it's no trouble.{\r}

790
01:23:03,327 --> 01:23:04,885
好吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah.{\r}

791
01:23:08,532 --> 01:23:12,969
我內心一直很掙扎，不知道該不該告訴你
{\fscx70\fscy70}I been holding a discussion with myself
over if I ought to tell you this or no.{\r}

792
01:23:13,137 --> 01:23:15,799
但最後我善良的一面贏了
{\fscx70\fscy70}My good side won out and...{\r}

793
01:23:17,008 --> 01:23:19,909
我想把事情說清楚
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I wanna make a clean breast
of things.{\r}

794
01:23:21,012 --> 01:23:25,176
可是我現在腦子還不太清楚
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, my mind's a little cobwebby
is the only drawback.{\r}

795
01:23:25,349 --> 01:23:30,150
我還想再…再睡一會
{\fscx70\fscy70}I could use a little...
A little more sleep.{\r}

796
01:23:32,690 --> 01:23:34,715
你知道我去了肯德基州吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know I went to Kentucky?{\r}

797
01:23:35,693 --> 01:23:37,126
知道
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah.{\r}

798
01:23:37,828 --> 01:23:40,262
我回來途經薩林縣
{\fscx70\fscy70}I come back through Saline County and...{\r}

799
01:23:41,665 --> 01:23:43,530
我想
{\fscx70\fscy70}...I think to myself:{\r}

800
01:23:44,068 --> 01:23:48,835
「不如去看看艾德·米勒吧？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}"Why not stop by and see Ed Miller?"{\r}

801
01:23:51,008 --> 01:23:52,737
我就去看了
{\fscx70\fscy70}So I do.{\r}

802
01:23:56,580 --> 01:23:59,913
不過結果我不太滿意
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, things are not to my satisfaction.{\r}

803
01:24:02,053 --> 01:24:04,817
艾德為了某些事，惶惶終日的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Ed's got himself all worked up
over something.{\r}

804
01:24:06,357 --> 01:24:09,622
我看得出來，他在扯謊
{\fscx70\fscy70}I can see that he's lying like a rug.{\r}

805
01:24:12,963 --> 01:24:16,057
我就對自己說，「適可而止吧」
{\fscx70\fscy70}So I say to myself, "Enough's enough."{\r}

806
01:24:16,567 --> 01:24:19,365
我對艾德說，「艾德」
{\fscx70\fscy70}And I say to Ed, "Come on, Ed.{\r}

807
01:24:20,304 --> 01:24:22,636
「咱們出去走走吧」
{\fscx70\fscy70}Let's go for a ride."{\r}

808
01:24:24,442 --> 01:24:27,343
你明白我說什麼嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You understand what I'm saying?{\r}

809
01:24:28,579 --> 01:24:31,548
出去走走就是
{\fscx70\fscy70}Going for a ride is like...{\r}

810
01:24:32,616 --> 01:24:35,744
出去走走就是給他苦頭吃的意思？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Going for a ride
is like giving him what-for?{\r}

811
01:24:37,721 --> 01:24:39,450
正是
{\fscx70\fscy70}Exactly.{\r}

812
01:24:43,928 --> 01:24:45,395
那麼…
{\fscx70\fscy70}So...{\r}

813
01:24:48,099 --> 01:24:49,964
艾德和傑西…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...Ed and Jesse...{\r}

814
01:24:52,369 --> 01:24:54,633
…在路上吵起來了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...they argue on the road.{\r}

815
01:24:59,076 --> 01:25:01,408
你有沒有數過星星？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Did you ever count the stars?{\r}

816
01:25:04,882 --> 01:25:08,818
我每次數的都不一樣，它們不停在變
{\fscx70\fscy70}I can't ever get the same number.
They keep changing on me.{\r}

817
01:25:10,688 --> 01:25:13,714
我連星星到底是什麼都不清楚
{\fscx70\fscy70}I don't even know what a star is exactly.{\r}

818
01:25:16,427 --> 01:25:18,622
你的身體知道
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, your body knows.{\r}

819
01:25:19,530 --> 01:25:21,998
只是你的心忘記了
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's your mind that forgot.{\r}

820
01:25:31,775 --> 01:25:34,835
你先走，我會追上你的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You go on ahead, partner.
I'll catch up with you.{\r}

821
01:26:15,052 --> 01:26:16,883
沒事
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's okay.{\r}

822
01:26:39,710 --> 01:26:43,168
沒事的，親愛的，沒事
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's okay, sweetheart. It's okay.{\r}

823
01:26:46,183 --> 01:26:48,651
吵到緊要關頭上
{\fscx70\fscy70}And when push came to shove...{\r}

824
01:26:55,526 --> 01:26:57,926
傑西一槍把艾德給斃了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...Jesse shot and killed him.{\r}

825
01:27:01,265 --> 01:27:03,130
傑西殺了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse did.{\r}

826
01:27:05,603 --> 01:27:07,332
你猜對了
{\fscx70\fscy70}You got it.{\r}

827
01:27:09,373 --> 01:27:10,738
你…
{\fscx70\fscy70}You...{\r}

828
01:27:27,324 --> 01:27:29,292
你看
{\fscx70\fscy70}So, you see, your...{\r}

829
01:27:29,493 --> 01:27:31,961
你堂弟，我沒拿他怎麼樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}Your cousin, he got off easy.{\r}

830
01:27:32,129 --> 01:27:33,721
只是跟他玩玩而已
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was just playing with Albert.{\r}

831
01:27:35,232 --> 01:27:38,895
是啊，我有時候也弄得他直嚷嚷
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, I made him squeal
once or twice myself.{\r}

832
01:27:39,203 --> 01:27:42,263
只是沒你那麼徹底而已
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm just not as thorough as you are.{\r}

833
01:27:53,550 --> 01:27:56,576
作為交換，你有故事要告訴我嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You got a tale to swap with me now?{\r}

834
01:28:05,362 --> 01:28:07,762
我不明白你意思
{\fscx70\fscy70}I don't get your meaning.{\r}

835
01:28:09,833 --> 01:28:15,135
我覺得，如果你也有什麼事情要坦白的話
{\fscx70\fscy70}Seems to me, if you have something
to confess in exchange...{\r}

836
01:28:15,306 --> 01:28:17,467
那你最好
{\fscx70\fscy70}...it'd only be right...{\r}

837
01:28:18,375 --> 01:28:21,708
現在就馬上告訴我
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that you'd spit it out now.{\r}

838
01:28:33,524 --> 01:28:35,651
我想不出有什麼事情
{\fscx70\fscy70}I can't think of a single thing.{\r}

839
01:28:38,562 --> 01:28:41,326
比如，伍德·海特？
{\fscx70\fscy70}About Wood Hite, for example.{\r}

840
01:28:41,498 --> 01:28:46,333
我不會…我不都跟你說了
我不知道他去哪了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm not gonna... I been saying over and
over I can't figure out where he's gone.{\r}

841
01:28:46,503 --> 01:28:49,563
我不能睜眼說瞎話啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}Now, I'm not gonna change my story
just to have something to spit.{\r}

842
01:28:49,740 --> 01:28:52,436
- 那為什麼你弟弟那麼不安？
- 哪個弟弟？
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Why was your brother so agitated?
- Which?{\r}

843
01:28:53,410 --> 01:28:54,502
鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob.{\r}

844
01:28:55,879 --> 01:28:58,871
他一向都那樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's just his way. He's antsy.{\r}

845
01:28:59,650 --> 01:29:01,083
知道吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know?{\r}

846
01:29:17,267 --> 01:29:19,861
你繼續睡覺吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}You go on back to sleep now.{\r}

847
01:29:21,505 --> 01:29:24,633
你現在倒讓我不安了
{\fscx70\fscy70}You got me agitated now, you see?{\r}

848
01:29:31,048 --> 01:29:35,246
是啊，傑西在的時候，誰都安定不得
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, just ain't no peace
when old Jesse's around.{\r}

849
01:29:35,786 --> 01:29:38,778
我老婆真可憐
{\fscx70\fscy70}You ought to pity my poor wife.{\r}

850
01:29:41,458 --> 01:29:43,619
艾德·米勒是我的好朋友
{\fscx70\fscy70}Ed Miller was a good friend of mine.{\r}

851
01:29:43,794 --> 01:29:47,230
有一次打撲克的時候
他把我介紹給你的
{\fscx70\fscy70}He introduced me to you
at that one poker game.{\r}

852
01:29:47,965 --> 01:29:51,992
你真那麼想聽實話的話
我就跟你說，我有點生你的氣
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm a little angry with you, if you
wanna know the God's honest truth.{\r}

853
01:29:54,471 --> 01:29:56,962
你也該可憐一下我
{\fscx70\fscy70}You ought to pity me too.{\r}

854
01:30:42,519 --> 01:30:46,455
為了證明和詹姆斯匪幫有聯繫
鮑勃告訴警方
{\fscx70\fscy70}As proof of his confederacy with
the James Gang, Bob told the authorities...{\r}

855
01:30:46,623 --> 01:30:50,115
迪克·利都正在一家租來的農舍
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that Dick Liddil was sleeping over
at the rented farmhouse...{\r}

856
01:30:50,294 --> 01:30:53,127
他的腿受傷了，在療傷
{\fscx70\fscy70}...while his ruined leg mended.{\r}

857
