{\fscx70\fscy70}He's gonna know I've been here with you.
You ought to take that for granted.{\r}

982
01:41:27,430 --> 01:41:31,389
一有機會他就會把你殺掉
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he will kill you if he gets the chance.{\r}

983
01:41:34,637 --> 01:41:37,197
你願意冒這個險嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Are you willing to risk that?{\r}

984
01:41:41,811 --> 01:41:43,540
願意
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yes, I am.{\r}

985
01:41:46,616 --> 01:41:48,345
我這輩子都那麼不起眼
{\fscx70\fscy70}I've been a nobody all my life.{\r}

986
01:41:49,285 --> 01:41:51,116
永遠當我是個小孩
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was the baby.{\r}

987
01:41:51,387 --> 01:41:54,823
答應我的事情也沒實現過
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was the one they made promises to
that they never kept.{\r}

988
01:41:56,025 --> 01:42:00,724
我記憶中
傑西·詹姆斯永遠那麼高大顯赫
{\fscx70\fscy70}And ever since I can remember it,
Jesse James has been as big as a tree.{\r}

989
01:42:04,167 --> 01:42:06,431
我準備好了，吉姆
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm prepared for this, Jim...{\r}

990
01:42:07,337 --> 01:42:09,498
我會完成任務的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I'm gonna accomplish it.{\r}

991
01:42:09,739 --> 01:42:11,832
我知道這是我唯一的機會
{\fscx70\fscy70}I know I won't get
but this one opportunity...{\r}

992
01:42:12,008 --> 01:42:14,909
我保證不會把這事毀了的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and you can bet your life
I'm not gonna spoil it.{\r}

993
01:42:26,923 --> 01:42:27,981
那麼…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well...{\r}

994
01:42:29,192 --> 01:42:31,183
等待合適的時機
{\fscx70\fscy70}...wait for your chance.{\r}

995
01:42:31,694 --> 01:42:35,095
別和他獨處，還有千萬…
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't let yourself be found alone with him,
and do not...{\r}

996
01:42:35,965 --> 01:42:38,365
不要讓他到你身後
{\fscx70\fscy70}...let him get behind you.{\r}

997
01:43:06,496 --> 01:43:07,690
你被選中了
{\fscx70\fscy70}You been chosen.{\r}

998
01:43:12,669 --> 01:43:14,261
什麼意思？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, what do you mean?{\r}

999
01:43:15,538 --> 01:43:18,029
你哥哥說你想加入我們
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, your brother said that
you might wanna join us.{\r}

1000
01:43:18,208 --> 01:43:21,541
不過，你對這雜貨店的感情
也許比嘴上說的更深
{\fscx70\fscy70}But maybe you like this grocery store
more than you said you did.{\r}

1001
01:43:24,847 --> 01:43:26,906
- 想我了？
- 對啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}- So you missed me?
- Oh, yeah.{\r}

1002
01:43:27,584 --> 01:43:30,246
每晚想你想到哭
{\fscx70\fscy70}I been crying myself to sleep every night.{\r}

1003
01:43:39,796 --> 01:43:41,787
別讓他看到我們倆
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't let him see us so much as wink.{\r}

1004
01:43:41,965 --> 01:43:45,799
他現在多疑得跟個野狼似的，誰也不信
{\fscx70\fscy70}He's suspicious as a damn coyote,
and he don't trust you one iota.{\r}

1005
01:43:46,502 --> 01:43:48,299
- 那我想…
- 嘿
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Well, I guess that makes...
- Hey.{\r}

1006
01:43:48,471 --> 01:43:52,931
他已經幹掉艾德·米勒了
還說得輕描淡寫的
{\fscx70\fscy70}He already put away Ed Miller. He said so
like it was something piddly he'd done.{\r}

1007
01:44:33,916 --> 01:44:38,148
如果我們倆能單獨待多過一分鐘
我很想再跟你談談
{\fscx70\fscy70}If we're ever alone for more than a minute,
I'd like a chance to talk to you further.{\r}

1008
01:45:17,894 --> 01:45:20,124
他們給我十天時間
{\fscx70\fscy70}They gave me ten days.{\r}

1009
01:45:24,000 --> 01:45:25,524
幹嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}For what?{\r}

1010
01:45:27,503 --> 01:45:29,368
逮捕他
{\fscx70\fscy70}For arresting him.{\r}

1011
01:45:35,445 --> 01:45:37,106
你和我?
{\fscx70\fscy70}You and me, huh?{\r}

1012
01:45:40,750 --> 01:45:44,015
不是他動手就是我們動手
這事躲不過的
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's gonna happen one way or another,
Charley. It's gonna happen.{\r}

1013
01:45:44,187 --> 01:45:46,781
幹嘛不趁這個機會撈點錢
{\fscx70\fscy70}So it might as well be us
who get rich on it.{\r}

1014
01:45:46,956 --> 01:45:50,255
- 鮑勃，他是我們的朋友
- 他殺了艾德·米勒
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Bob, he's our friend.
- He murdered Ed Miller.{\r}

1015
01:45:50,893 --> 01:45:53,987
一有機會，他就會去殺利都和康明斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he's gonna murder Liddil and Cummins
if the chance ever comes.{\r}

1016
01:45:55,431 --> 01:46:00,061
照我看來，傑西正一個個地
把幫裡的兄弟做掉
{\fscx70\fscy70}It seems to me Jesse's riding from
man to man, saying goodbye to the gang.{\r}

1017
01:46:01,571 --> 01:46:03,937
你的友情會害死你的
{\fscx70\fscy70}So your friendship could put you
under the pansies.{\r}

1018
01:46:06,008 --> 01:46:10,468
我會認真考慮的，鮑勃
我現在只能到這一步了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'll grind it fine in my mind, Bob. I can't
go any further than that right now.{\r}

1019
01:46:14,050 --> 01:46:15,483
你會想通的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You'll come around.{\r}

1020
01:46:16,619 --> 01:46:19,087
你認為這都是編造的，是嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think it's all made up, don't you?{\r}

1021
01:46:19,255 --> 01:46:22,588
他的故事只是報紙編的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think it's all yarns
and newspaper stories.{\r}

1022
01:46:30,466 --> 01:46:32,798
他也不過是個人
{\fscx70\fscy70}He's just a human being.{\r}

1023
01:46:41,043 --> 01:46:44,171
從今以後，你們倆不許離開我行動
{\fscx70\fscy70}From now on, you two
won't go anywhere without me.{\r}

1024
01:46:44,947 --> 01:46:49,509
從今以後，你們的行動要得到我批准！
要向我請示！
{\fscx70\fscy70}From now on, you'll ask for my permission!
From now on, you'll ask to be excused!{\r}

1025
01:47:45,441 --> 01:47:49,741
查理，把馬帶到馬棚裡
鮑勃，進屋去吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley, take them horses
around the barn. Bob, you go on inside.{\r}

1026
01:47:50,580 --> 01:47:51,911
- 你好，瑪麗
- 嗨
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Hello, Mary.
- Hi.{\r}

1027
01:47:52,081 --> 01:47:55,244
看我在堆肥裡找到的蘿蔔(歐洲蘿蔔）
{\fscx70\fscy70}Look at this rotten parsnip
I found in the compost heap.{\r}

1028
01:48:05,461 --> 01:48:07,361
你沒提過鮑勃會來
{\fscx70\fscy70}You never mentioned Bob would be here.{\r}

1029
01:48:11,634 --> 01:48:14,626
可能他想留作驚喜呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}Maybe he was saving it
as a pleasant surprise.{\r}

1030
01:48:19,242 --> 01:48:21,904
現在來了兩位堂兄弟做伴了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Got two cousins for company now.{\r}

1031
01:48:31,621 --> 01:48:33,919
這麼著…
{\fscx70\fscy70}How it's gonna be is...{\r}

1032
01:48:34,290 --> 01:48:38,488
我們下週一下午離開，到普拉特市
{\fscx70\fscy70}...we'll leave next Monday afternoon
and ride down to Platte City.{\r}

1033
01:48:41,364 --> 01:48:43,298
離堪薩斯市多遠？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How far is that from Kansas City?{\r}

1034
01:48:45,001 --> 01:48:47,834
往南三十英里
{\fscx70\fscy70}Platte City's 30 miles south.{\r}

1035
01:48:49,472 --> 01:48:54,068
你，我和查理晚上在森林裡睡一夜
{\fscx70\fscy70}You and me and Charley'll
sleep in the woods overnight...{\r}

1036
01:48:54,577 --> 01:48:58,980
我們會在關門之前一段時間
進攻富國銀行
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and we'll strike the Wells Bank
sometime before the court recesses.{\r}

1037
01:49:03,786 --> 01:49:06,721
具體是幾點？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What time will that be exactly?{\r}

1038
01:49:12,361 --> 01:49:14,886
這你沒必要知道
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you don't need to know that.{\r}

1039
01:49:29,912 --> 01:49:32,881
我和你哥哥一起的時候很愜意
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know, I'm real comfortable
with your brother.{\r}

1040
01:49:33,115 --> 01:49:35,640
雖然他長得難看，身上也臭
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hell, he's ugly as sin,
he smells like a skunk...{\r}

1041
01:49:36,452 --> 01:49:39,888
還無知得要命
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and he's so ignorant
he couldn't drive nails in the snow...{\r}

1042
01:49:40,056 --> 01:49:42,547
但他很好相處
{\fscx70\fscy70}...but he's sort of easy to be around.{\r}

1043
01:49:43,059 --> 01:49:45,857
你就不一樣了，鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}I can't say the same for you, Bob.{\r}

1044
01:49:49,265 --> 01:49:51,631
你這麼說讓我很難過
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I'm sorry to hear you say that.{\r}

1045
01:49:53,502 --> 01:49:57,529
你知道那種情況吧
你和你愛人在月色之下
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know how it is when you're
with your girlfriend and the moon's out...{\r}

1046
01:49:57,707 --> 01:50:01,768
雖然她從沒開口說
但你知道她等著你親她
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and you know she wants to be kissed,
even though she never said so?{\r}

1047
01:50:05,181 --> 01:50:06,614
恩
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah.{\r}

1048
01:50:09,352 --> 01:50:12,719
你的種種跡象，讓我很難過
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you're giving me signs
that grieve my soul...{\r}

1049
01:50:13,589 --> 01:50:15,716
讓我覺得…
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and make me wonder...{\r}

1050
01:50:16,125 --> 01:50:18,491
可能你對我的看法已經變了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...maybe your mind's
been changed about me.{\r}

1051
01:50:18,828 --> 01:50:22,286
你要我怎麼辦？向天發誓？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, what do you want me to do?
Swear my good faith on the Bible?{\r}

1052
01:50:39,782 --> 01:50:41,716
你倆在吵架？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You two having a spat?{\r}

1053
01:50:46,989 --> 01:50:49,480
我正準備發火呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was getting ready to be angry.{\r}

1054
01:50:54,964 --> 01:50:57,296
坐過來點，孩子
{\fscx70\fscy70}Sit over here closer, kid.{\r}

1055
01:50:59,535 --> 01:51:00,797
過來過來
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on.{\r}

1056
01:51:11,947 --> 01:51:14,279
查理，到時你看著馬
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley, you'll stay with the animals.{\r}

1057
01:51:14,950 --> 01:51:16,850
我和這孩子
{\fscx70\fscy70}Me and the kid...{\r}

1058
01:51:17,019 --> 01:51:20,978
會在中午之前走進那銀行
{\fscx70\fscy70}...will walk into that bank
just before noon.{\r}

1059
01:51:22,858 --> 01:51:25,486
鮑勃會讓那出納員
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob will move that cashier...{\r}

1060
01:51:26,028 --> 01:51:29,259
沒法拿到櫃檯底下藏著的槍
{\fscx70\fscy70}...away from the shotgun
that's under the counter...{\r}

1061
01:51:29,432 --> 01:51:32,299
然後我就溜到那出納員後頭
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I'll creep up behind that cashier...{\r}

1062
01:51:32,468 --> 01:51:34,800
這樣把他的頭朝後扳
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I'll cock his head back like so.{\r}

1063
01:51:35,071 --> 01:51:36,095
我會說
{\fscx70\fscy70}And I'll say:{\r}

1064
01:51:36,272 --> 01:51:39,002
「像你這樣的廢柴怎麼還活著
{\fscx70\fscy70}"How come an off-scouring
like you is still sucking air...{\r}

1065
01:51:39,175 --> 01:51:41,439
而我那麼多手下就已經送命了呢？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}...when so many of mine
are in coffins?" I'll say:{\r}

1066
01:51:41,610 --> 01:51:44,943
「你怎麼還能活到20歲？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}"How did you get to reach 20
without leaking out all over your clothes?"{\r}

1067
01:51:45,414 --> 01:51:49,282
如果我不喜歡他的態度
我會狠狠地割掉那小子的喉嚨
{\fscx70\fscy70}And if I don't like his attitude,
I will slit that phildoodle so deep...{\r}

1068
01:51:49,585 --> 01:51:52,611
讓他像條脫水的魚一樣亂跳
{\fscx70\fscy70}...he will flop on the floor like a fish.{\r}

1069
01:51:56,292 --> 01:51:58,658
天啊，發生什麼了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}My God, what just happened?{\r}

1070
01:52:07,903 --> 01:52:11,270
鮑勃，我能聽到你的小腦袋發動了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Boy, I could hear your gears grinding...{\r}

1071
01:52:11,574 --> 01:52:14,941
聽到你在問自己
「天啊，下次他會幹出什麼事？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}...hear your little motor wondering,
"My gosh, what's next?{\r}

1072
01:52:15,111 --> 01:52:16,476
「我會怎麼樣？」
{\fscx70\fscy70}What's happening to me?"{\r}

1073
01:52:18,347 --> 01:52:20,212
看你這樣子，鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}You were precious to behold, Bob.{\r}

1074
01:52:20,382 --> 01:52:23,010
臉白得跟牆一樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}You were white as spit in a cotton field.{\r}

1075
01:52:23,552 --> 01:52:26,020
你嚇到他了
{\fscx70\fscy70}You got him. You got him.{\r}

1076
01:52:27,656 --> 01:52:31,717
你想知道這是什麼感覺嗎？不舒服
我真的不推薦你這麼做
{\fscx70\fscy70}You wanna know how that feels?
Unpleasant. I honestly can't recommend it.{\r}

1077
01:52:37,233 --> 01:52:39,701
查理看來也被嚇倒了
{\fscx70\fscy70}The old Charley looked stricken!{\r}

1078
01:52:40,369 --> 01:52:42,200
是啊，是啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was. I was.{\r}

1079
01:52:42,371 --> 01:52:47,365
「太恐怖了」，查理想道
「把我一天的心情都毀了」
{\fscx70\fscy70}"This is plumb unexpected," old Charley
was thinking. "That done ruined my day."{\r}

1080
01:52:55,151 --> 01:52:56,584
天呀
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hell. Hell.{\r}

1081
01:53:27,550 --> 01:53:31,418
那晚，傑西和鮑勃睡在孩子們的房間
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse slept with Bob
in the children's room that night.{\r}

1082
01:53:32,721 --> 01:53:35,315
鮑勃一直醒著
{\fscx70\fscy70}And Bob remained awake.{\r}

1083
01:53:38,160 --> 01:53:41,527
他能看到床頭櫃上有一把槍
{\fscx70\fscy70}He could see that there was a gun
on the nightstand.{\r}

1084
01:53:42,398 --> 01:53:46,391
他能想像自己手裡握著冰冷的槍
{\fscx70\fscy70}He could imagine its cold nickel
inside his grip...{\r}

1085
01:53:47,303 --> 01:53:50,795
舉起這兩磅的重量，瞄準
{\fscx70\fscy70}...its two-pound weight
reached out and aimed.{\r}

1086
01:54:21,937 --> 01:54:24,030
我要上廁所
{\fscx70\fscy70}I need to go to the privy.{\r}

1087
01:54:25,241 --> 01:54:28,642
你以為你要上，但其實你不用上
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think you do, but you don't.{\r}

1088
01:54:51,867 --> 01:54:54,028
等禱告之後再吃
{\fscx70\fscy70}You wait for grace, now.{\r}

1089
01:54:54,970 --> 01:54:58,303
- 謝謝，媽媽
- 謝謝，芝，看來很好吃哦
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Thank you, Mama.
- Thank you, Zee. God, that looks good.{\r}

1090
01:54:58,474 --> 01:55:00,101
- 謝謝，芝
- 不客氣
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Thank you, Zee.
- You're welcome.{\r}

1091
01:55:00,276 --> 01:55:03,370
這適合吃還是湊合？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, is this fit to eat or will it just do?{\r}

1092
01:55:06,282 --> 01:55:08,375
她做飯可是臭名遠播
{\fscx70\fscy70}Woman's cooking's
always been a scandal.{\r}

1093
01:55:08,550 --> 01:55:10,916
她做的肉，切起來整張桌子都得晃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Cut her meat and the whole table moves.{\r}

1094
01:55:11,854 --> 01:55:13,913
想吃餅幹嗎？想要嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You want a biscuit?
You gonna have a biscuit?{\r}

1095
01:55:14,089 --> 01:55:17,889
給你黃油，來
{\fscx70\fscy70}Here's some butter.
Come on. Come on.{\r}

1096
01:55:19,828 --> 01:55:21,125
哦，媽的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, shoot.{\r}

1097
01:55:21,297 --> 01:55:25,097
傑西變得越來越平易近人
{\fscx70\fscy70}And so it went,
Jesse was increasingly cavalier...{\r}

1098
01:55:25,267 --> 01:55:28,998
和藹，情緒化，沉鬱
{\fscx70\fscy70}...merry, moody, fey...{\r}

1099
01:55:29,171 --> 01:55:31,264
不可預測
{\fscx70\fscy70}...unpredictable.{\r}

1100
01:55:32,808 --> 01:55:35,936
他把抑鬱和狂亂隱藏起來
{\fscx70\fscy70}He camouflaged his depressions
and derangements...{\r}

1101
01:55:36,111 --> 01:55:40,104
用高度的誠懇和風度來掩飾
{\fscx70\fscy70}...with masquerades
of extreme cordiality, courtesy...{\r}

1102
01:55:40,282 --> 01:55:43,046
假裝對人好心好意
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and goodwill towards others.{\r}

1103
01:55:44,119 --> 01:55:48,385
但即使他開玩笑的時候
或者給他兒子呵癢的時候
{\fscx70\fscy70}But even as he jested,
or tickled his boy in the ribs...{\r}

1104
01:55:48,557 --> 01:55:52,186
傑西都會用憂鬱的眼神看著鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}...Jesse would look over at Bob
with melancholy eyes...{\r}

1105
01:55:52,361 --> 01:55:56,320
兩人彷彿在進行親密深邃的交流
{\fscx70\fscy70}...as if the two were meshed
in an intimate communication.{\r}

1106
01:55:59,134 --> 01:56:01,762
鮑勃堅信傑西看穿了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob was certain that the man
had unriddled him...{\r}

1107
01:56:01,937 --> 01:56:04,599
看穿了他為什麼跟來
{\fscx70\fscy70}...had seen through his reasons
for coming along...{\r}

1108
01:56:04,773 --> 01:56:08,766
堅信傑西能預測鮑勃任何的行動和企圖
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that Jesse could forecast each of
Bob's possible moves and inclinations...{\r}

1109
01:56:08,944 --> 01:56:10,775
傑西只是在扮無辜
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and was only acting the innocent...{\r}

1110
01:56:10,946 --> 01:56:15,883
好讓鮑勃放鬆警惕
{\fscx70\fscy70}...in order to lull Bob
into stupid tranquility and miscalculation.{\r}

1111
01:56:37,573 --> 01:56:39,768
你盯著我看多久了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How long you been studying me?{\r}

1112
01:56:41,677 --> 01:56:44,407
你會讓很多人傷心的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're gonna break a lot of hearts.{\r}

1113
01:56:52,321 --> 01:56:53,515
什麼意思？
{\fscx70\fscy70}How do you mean?{\r}

1114
01:57:02,765 --> 01:57:04,494
是份禮物
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's a present.{\r}

1115
01:57:09,171 --> 01:57:10,729
很沉
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's heavy.{\r}

1116
01:57:11,306 --> 01:57:13,433
打開看看？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you gonna look inside?{\r}

1117
01:57:15,010 --> 01:57:16,807
今天是愚人節
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's April Fools' Day, you know.{\r}

1118
01:57:17,379 --> 01:57:19,210
這可不是個玩笑
{\fscx70\fscy70}It ain't no joke.{\r}

1119
01:57:26,722 --> 01:57:28,280
太華麗了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, such extravagance.{\r}

1120
01:57:29,825 --> 01:57:32,521
閃亮亮的，是吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't that nickel just shine, though?{\r}

1121
01:57:32,728 --> 01:57:34,286
我做夢都沒想過
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's more than I could hope for.{\r}

1122
01:57:34,463 --> 01:57:37,261
你那老破槍，說不定下次開槍的時候
{\fscx70\fscy70}I figured that granddaddy Colt
may blow into fragments...{\r}

1123
01:57:37,433 --> 01:57:40,197
就得崩成一塊一塊的了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...next time you try
to squeeze the trigger.{\r}

1124
01:57:40,436 --> 01:57:42,836
你也許說的對
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, you might have something there.{\r}

1125
01:57:43,338 --> 01:57:45,966
湯姆，飯好了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Tom, supper's ready.{\r}

1126
01:57:47,142 --> 01:57:49,167
馬上來，親愛的
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'll be right there, sweetheart.{\r}

1127
01:57:49,344 --> 01:57:51,642
我太興奮了，都吃不下飯了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I might be too excited to eat.{\r}

1128
01:57:54,917 --> 01:57:57,408
你知道約翰·紐曼·愛德華茲
曾經怎麼寫我嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know what John Newman Edwards
once wrote about me?{\r}

1129
01:57:58,454 --> 01:58:01,287
他說，給我一萬個人
我只能找出兩個能信任的人
{\fscx70\fscy70}He said I didn't trust
two men in 10,000...{\r}

1130
01:58:01,457 --> 01:58:04,119
就算和這倆人一起，我還是很警惕
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and even them I was cautious around.{\r}

1131
01:58:04,927 --> 01:58:06,918
政府長年追捕，讓我疲憊不堪
{\fscx70\fscy70}Government's sort of run me ragged.{\r}

1132
01:58:08,897 --> 01:58:11,889
我繞著圈子說話呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm going the long way around the barn
to say that...{\r}

1133
01:58:12,067 --> 01:58:15,696
我是被追急了，最近有時故意刁難人
{\fscx70\fscy70}...I been feeling cornered
and just plain ornery as of late...{\r}

1134
01:58:16,438 --> 01:58:21,102
如果你能接受這把槍，接受我的歉意
我會很高興的
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I'd be pleased if you'd accept
that gun as my way of apologizing.{\r}

1135
01:58:23,479 --> 01:58:26,277
如果我是你，我大概會更加刁難人
{\fscx70\fscy70}Heaven knows I'd be ornerier
if I were in your position.{\r}

1136
01:58:26,448 --> 01:58:29,542
不，不，我的行為是不對的
{\fscx70\fscy70}No. No, I haven't been acting correctly.{\r}

1137
01:58:31,353 --> 01:58:34,880
我有時候都認不出自己了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Seems I hardly recognize myself
when I'm greased.{\r}

1138
01:58:37,960 --> 01:58:40,451
我有時候靈魂出竅
{\fscx70\fscy70}I go on journeys out of my body...{\r}

1139
01:58:40,629 --> 01:58:44,725
看到自己這染血的手和兇惡的臉
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and look at my red hands
and my mean face...{\r}

1140
01:58:45,501 --> 01:58:49,232
看著這個做了那麼多錯事的人
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and I wonder about that man
that's gone so wrong.{\r}

1141
01:58:53,008 --> 01:58:56,034
我對自己來說，都已經成了一個麻煩
{\fscx70\fscy70}I've been becoming a problem to myself.{\r}

1142
01:59:08,690 --> 01:59:10,055
唉
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well...{\r}

1143
01:59:16,698 --> 01:59:21,328
- 該吃飯了，我去洗手
- 恩，去吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}- I better wash my hands if supper's on.
- Yeah, go ahead.{\r}

1144
01:59:34,683 --> 01:59:37,618
他死前一天是主進聖城節
{\fscx70\fscy70}The day before he died was Palm Sunday.{\r}

1145
01:59:38,654 --> 01:59:41,953
湯瑪斯·霍華德先生和他的夫人，
還有他們的兩個孩子
{\fscx70\fscy70}And Mr. And Mrs. Thomas Howard,
their two children...{\r}

1146
01:59:42,124 --> 01:59:44,183
還有他們的表親查爾斯·約翰森
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and their cousin Charles Johnson...{\r}

1147
01:59:44,359 --> 01:59:49,524
到第二長老會教堂參加10點的禮拜
{\fscx70\fscy70}...strolled to the Second Presbyterian
Church to attend the 10:00 service.{\r}

1148
01:59:51,934 --> 01:59:54,232
鮑勃留在了屋裡
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob remained at the cottage...{\r}

1149
01:59:54,403 --> 01:59:57,804
偷偷地從一個房間，走到另一個房間
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and slyly migrated from room to room.{\r}

1150
02:00:00,409 --> 02:00:02,240
他走進主人房
{\fscx70\fscy70}He walked into the master bedroom...{\r}

1151
02:00:02,411 --> 02:00:06,177
把裡面的衣服翻了一遍
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and inventoried the clothes
on the hangers and hooks.{\r}

1152
02:00:12,487 --> 02:00:15,820
拿起化妝台上的一杯水，喝了一口
{\fscx70\fscy70}He sipped from the water glass
on the vanity.{\r}

1153
02:00:18,160 --> 02:00:22,426
聞了聞傑西枕套上的滑石粉和丁香花
{\fscx70\fscy70}He smelled the talcum and lilacs
on Jesse's pillowcase.{\r}

1154
02:00:30,339 --> 02:00:32,534
他的手指滑過自己的肋骨
{\fscx70\fscy70}His fingers skittered over his ribs...{\r}

1155
02:00:32,708 --> 02:00:36,576
想像上面像傑西那樣，有兩次中槍的傷疤
{\fscx70\fscy70}...to construe the scars
where Jesse was twice shot.{\r}

1156
02:00:40,382 --> 02:00:44,978
他把中指弄成上兩個關節沒了那樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}He manufactured a middle finger
that was missing the top two knuckles.{\r}

1157
02:00:52,427 --> 02:00:55,362
想像自己34歲
{\fscx70\fscy70}He imagined himself at 34.{\r}

1158
02:00:57,366 --> 02:01:00,358
想像自己躺在了棺材裡
{\fscx70\fscy70}He imagined himself in a coffin.{\r}

1159
02:01:02,437 --> 02:01:04,166
他想到各種各樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}He considered possibilities...{\r}

1160
02:01:04,339 --> 02:01:07,638
即將成真的好事情
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and everything wonderful
that could come true.{\r}

1161
02:01:35,437 --> 02:01:37,371
他不會殺我們的
{\fscx70\fscy70}He's not gonna kill us.{\r}

1162
02:01:42,611 --> 02:01:44,772
他會的
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, he is.{\r}

1163
02:01:47,082 --> 02:01:49,573
我會一直醒著，他就沒法下手了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, I'll stay awake so he can't.{\r}

1164
02:02:02,931 --> 02:02:05,365
你在瞎想
{\fscx70\fscy70}You're imagining things.{\r}

1165
02:02:17,612 --> 02:02:19,580
不會去什麼普拉特市
{\fscx70\fscy70}Ain't gonna be no Platte City.{\r}

1166
02:02:21,316 --> 02:02:23,944
傑西只是在耍我們
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's Jesse fooling with us.{\r}

1167
02:02:40,369 --> 02:02:42,599
睡吧，查理
{\fscx70\fscy70}Go to sleep, Charley.{\r}

1168
02:02:54,200 --> 02:02:57,200
[1882年4月3日]

1169
02:03:16,204 --> 02:03:17,796
早
{\fscx70\fscy70}Morning.{\r}

1170
02:03:21,610 --> 02:03:23,134
查理
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley.{\r}

1171
02:03:52,974 --> 02:03:55,408
鮑勃，你要吃多少？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob, how much did you want to eat?{\r}

1172
02:03:59,915 --> 02:04:02,349
我感覺有點怪怪的
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm feeling sort of peculiar.{\r}

1173
02:04:21,570 --> 02:04:24,038
為什麼那麼感興趣地看著我們？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why is it you're looking so interested?{\r}

1174
02:04:25,507 --> 02:04:28,408
你以為這樣出去晃很聰明？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You think it's intelligent
to go out like that...{\r}

1175
02:04:28,577 --> 02:04:30,408
讓大家都看見你的槍？
{\fscx70\fscy70}...so all creation can see your guns?{\r}

1176
02:04:48,163 --> 02:04:49,596
嗨
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hi.{\r}

1177
02:04:59,908 --> 02:05:02,809
來，看你媽媽在幹嗎
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on, let's go see
what your mama's doing.{\r}

1178
02:05:03,945 --> 02:05:06,072
提米，開門
{\fscx70\fscy70}Timmy, get that door, would you?{\r}

1179
02:05:10,218 --> 02:05:13,381
- 你弄丟了一隻鞋是嗎，親愛的
- 是啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Well, you lost your shoe, sweetheart.
- Yeah, I did.{\r}

1180
02:05:13,555 --> 02:05:17,685
那可麻煩了，商店也不單只賣呀
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's gonna be a problem.
They don't sell those one at a time.{\r}

1181
02:05:19,194 --> 02:05:21,253
我們丟了一隻鞋，媽媽
{\fscx70\fscy70}We lost a shoe, Mama.{\r}

1182
02:05:22,864 --> 02:05:25,424
幫爸爸穿上，好嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Will you put that up for Daddy,
would you?{\r}

1183
02:05:28,503 --> 02:05:31,267
- 你在幹嗎，丟了一隻鞋？
- 恩
{\fscx70\fscy70}- What you doing, you lose a shoe?
- Yeah.{\r}

1184
02:05:34,782 --> 02:05:38,488
[迪克·利都被逮捕，並已認罪]

1185
02:05:47,989 --> 02:05:51,390
只會往上，作為補充
{\fscx70\fscy70}It's only meant to go on top,
to complement.{\r}

1186
02:05:51,660 --> 02:05:53,491
我知道，有時候，我
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah, I know. Sometimes, l...{\r}

1187
02:06:18,086 --> 02:06:20,987
鮑勃，菜要涼了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob, everything's getting cold!{\r}

1188
02:06:21,690 --> 02:06:25,091
- 瑪麗在哪裡？
- 在外面，親愛的
{\fscx70\fscy70}- Where's Mary?
- She's outside, darling.{\r}

1189
02:06:26,094 --> 02:06:27,891
瑪麗？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Mary?{\r}

1190
02:06:31,666 --> 02:06:34,191
你說他那小腦瓜裡都在想什麼？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What do you think goes on
in that noggin of his?{\r}

1191
02:06:37,205 --> 02:06:38,900
沒什麼
{\fscx70\fscy70}Nothing.{\r}

1192
02:06:39,474 --> 02:06:42,272
我說的是他，不是你
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was talking about his mind, not yours.{\r}

1193
02:06:43,211 --> 02:06:44,940
哦，是啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, yeah.{\r}

1194
02:06:45,380 --> 02:06:47,075
哈，我明白
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, I get it.{\r}

1195
02:07:42,504 --> 02:07:44,472
啊哈
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, hello now.{\r}

1196
02:07:44,873 --> 02:07:47,899
「迪克·利都被逮捕，並已認罪」
{\fscx70\fscy70}"The arrest and confession
of Dick Liddil."{\r}

1197
02:07:53,148 --> 02:07:55,309
不是吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}You don't say so.{\r}

1198
02:08:09,631 --> 02:08:11,724
真怪了
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's very strange.{\r}

1199
02:08:12,167 --> 02:08:15,068
上面說迪克三星期前就投降了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Says here Dick surrendered
three weeks ago.{\r}

1200
02:08:15,236 --> 02:08:17,830
那時候你應該在那附近吧
{\fscx70\fscy70}You must have been
right in the neighborhood.{\r}

1201
02:08:18,506 --> 02:08:21,134
很明顯，他們是秘密行動
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, apparently, they kept it a secret.{\r}

1202
02:08:32,353 --> 02:08:35,413
如果我短期內去堪薩斯市，會找人問問
{\fscx70\fscy70}If I get to Kansas City soon,
I'll ask somebody about it.{\r}

1203
02:09:16,097 --> 02:09:17,792
你倆準備好了嗎
{\fscx70\fscy70}You two ready?{\r}

1204
02:09:21,503 --> 02:09:24,165
馬上就好
{\fscx70\fscy70}I will be, by noon.{\r}

1205
02:09:57,071 --> 02:09:59,733
她要上船，航行出海
{\fscx70\fscy70}There is a ship
She sails the sea{\r}

1206
02:09:59,908 --> 02:10:02,672
她裝了很多很多東西
{\fscx70\fscy70}She's loaded deep
As deep can be{\r}

1207
02:10:02,844 --> 02:10:05,074
但不及我對她的愛多
{\fscx70\fscy70}But not as deep
As the love I'm in{\r}

1208
02:10:05,647 --> 02:10:09,276
我不知道我是浮是沉
{\fscx70\fscy70}I know not if I sink or swim{\r}

1209
02:10:10,318 --> 02:10:12,013
海水廣闊
{\fscx70\fscy70}The water is wide{\r}

1210
02:10:13,154 --> 02:10:19,718
我游不過，也沒法翱翔而過
{\fscx70\fscy70}I can't cross o'er
And neither have I wings to fly{\r}

1211
02:10:20,161 --> 02:10:23,961
給我一隻能載兩個人的小船
{\fscx70\fscy70}Give me a boat
That can carry two{\r}

1212
02:10:24,132 --> 02:10:26,999
一起划船，我和我的愛人
{\fscx70\fscy70}Both shall row
My love and I{\r}

1213
02:10:27,168 --> 02:10:30,626
柔情款款
{\fscx70\fscy70}For love is gentle
And love is kind{\r}

1214
02:10:30,805 --> 02:10:33,797
如初開花蕾，芬芳撲鼻
{\fscx70\fscy70}Sweetest flower
When first it's new{\r}

1215
02:10:33,975 --> 02:10:37,570
但熱情一旦冷卻
{\fscx70\fscy70}But love grows old
And waxes cold{\r}

1216
02:10:37,745 --> 02:10:40,976
就像晨露一樣枯萎
{\fscx70\fscy70}And fades away
Like the morning dew{\r}

1217
02:10:41,149 --> 02:10:44,175
她要上船，航行出海
{\fscx70\fscy70}There is a ship
She sails the sea{\r}

1218
02:10:44,352 --> 02:10:47,116
我該把槍拿下來
{\fscx70\fscy70}I guess I'll take my guns off...{\r}

1219
02:10:47,455 --> 02:10:49,446
別讓鄰居看到
{\fscx70\fscy70}...for fear the neighbors might spy them.{\r}

1220
02:11:22,757 --> 02:11:25,191
這畫怎麼那麼多灰？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Don't that picture look dusty?{\r}

1221
02:13:07,295 --> 02:13:10,287
你…你做了什麼？
{\fscx70\fscy70}What have...? What have you done?{\r}

1222
02:13:12,734 --> 02:13:14,361
傑西
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse.{\r}

1223
02:13:19,907 --> 02:13:20,931
傑西？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse?{\r}

1224
02:13:22,076 --> 02:13:24,203
傑西？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse? Jesse?{\r}

1225
02:13:24,946 --> 02:13:26,811
傑西！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse!{\r}

1226
02:13:27,815 --> 02:13:29,908
不!
{\fscx70\fscy70}No!{\r}

1227
02:13:34,088 --> 02:13:36,420
別，傑西
{\fscx70\fscy70}No. Jess...{\r}

1228
02:13:37,025 --> 02:13:41,428
回來，回來
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come back. Oh, come back.{\r}

1229
02:13:43,564 --> 02:13:47,728
傑西，不要！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, Jesse! No!{\r}

1230
02:13:48,236 --> 02:13:52,138
鮑勃，是你幹的嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Oh, Bob. Have you done this?!{\r}

1231
02:13:52,340 --> 02:13:54,706
我向上帝發誓，我沒有
{\fscx70\fscy70}I swear to God I didn't.{\r}

1232
02:13:55,710 --> 02:13:57,143
是場意外，芝
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was an accident, Zee.{\r}

1233
02:13:59,347 --> 02:14:02,714
槍走火了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on. Pistol went off accidentally.{\r}

1234
02:14:48,062 --> 02:14:49,256
