02:14:49,430 --> 02:14:51,898
[州長：我殺了傑西·詹姆斯。羅伯特·福特]
你做什麼了？我殺了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why, what'd you do? I shot him.{\r}

1236
02:14:59,107 --> 02:15:01,132
你大概會想留著它
{\fscx70\fscy70}You might wanna keep that.{\r}

1237
02:15:39,080 --> 02:15:41,173
謝謝
{\fscx70\fscy70}Thank you all very much.{\r}

1238
02:15:49,323 --> 02:15:51,814
照片以每張２美元的價錢賣出
{\fscx70\fscy70}The resulting prints
sold for 2 dollars apiece...{\r}

1239
02:15:51,993 --> 02:15:56,589
好些雜誌拿來做了封面
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and were the models for the lithographed
covers on a number of magazines.{\r}

1240
02:16:02,136 --> 02:16:07,335
成千的陌生人像著了魔一樣
來到這房子來朝聖
{\fscx70\fscy70}Soon a thousand strangers were making
spellbound pilgrimages to the cottage...{\r}

1241
02:16:07,708 --> 02:16:12,236
到森丹法鄧的冷藏室去瞻仰
{\fscx70\fscy70}...or were venerating the iced remains
in Seidenfaden's cooling room.{\r}

1242
02:16:13,147 --> 02:16:17,641
有個人，曾經出價３萬美元，想買下
刺殺加菲爾德·詹姆士總統那殺手的屍體
{\fscx70\fscy70}The man who offered 30,000 dollars for
the body of President Garfield's assassin...{\r}

1243
02:16:17,818 --> 02:16:21,720
他給該市警長克雷格打了個電報，出價５萬
{\fscx70\fscy70}...sent a telegram to City Marshal
Enos Craig offering 50,000...{\r}

1244
02:16:21,889 --> 02:16:24,187
想買下傑西·詹姆斯的遺體
{\fscx70\fscy70}...for the body
of Jesse Woodson James...{\r}

1245
02:16:24,358 --> 02:16:27,122
準備全國展覽
{\fscx70\fscy70}...so that he could go around the country
with it...{\r}

1246
02:16:29,530 --> 02:16:34,490
或者至少賣給P·T·巴納姆，在其表演裡展出
（美國著名遊藝節目演出的經理人）
{\fscx70\fscy70}...or at least sell it to P.T. Barnum
for his Greatest Show on Earth.{\r}

1247
02:16:38,573 --> 02:16:41,667
另外一張照片，拍的是這位美國著名大盜
{\fscx70\fscy70}Another photograph was taken
of the renowned American bandit...{\r}

1248
02:16:41,842 --> 02:16:44,436
躺在冰床上
{\fscx70\fscy70}...nestled in his bed of ice.{\r}

1249
02:16:44,612 --> 02:16:48,878
這張照片在小店和藥房等地方都大賣
{\fscx70\fscy70}And it was this shot that was most
available in sundries and apothecaries...{\r}

1250
02:16:49,050 --> 02:16:52,713
大家透過立體透鏡來看這照片
就像看獅身人面像
{\fscx70\fscy70}...to be viewed in a stereoscope
alongside the sphinx...{\r}

1251
02:16:52,887 --> 02:16:56,880
泰姬陵和羅馬的地下墓室
這些名勝古跡的照片一樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}...the Taj Mahal,
and the catacombs of Rome.{\r}

1252
02:17:22,083 --> 02:17:24,051
看啊
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hello, here!{\r}

1253
02:17:24,252 --> 02:17:26,846
「迪克·利都被逮捕，並已認罪」
{\fscx70\fscy70}"The arrest and confession
of Dick Liddil."{\r}

1254
02:17:27,021 --> 02:17:32,152
年輕人，你跟我說過
不知道迪克投降了是吧？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Young man, I thought you told me
you didn't know Dick had surrendered.{\r}

1255
02:17:32,326 --> 02:17:36,194
真的嗎？我不知道
{\fscx70\fscy70}You mean he did? I didn't know.{\r}

1256
02:17:37,098 --> 02:17:38,998
但我知道我騙不了他
{\fscx70\fscy70}But I knew I had not fooled him.{\r}

1257
02:17:39,166 --> 02:17:43,000
他和我一樣心知肚明，那一刻我準備
把他繩之於法
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he knew, as well as I, in that moment
that I intended to bring him to justice.{\r}

1258
02:17:43,938 --> 02:17:47,499
但他不會當著他老婆孩子的面殺我
{\fscx70\fscy70}But he would not kill me
in the presence of his wife and children.{\r}

1259
02:17:47,675 --> 02:17:50,906
所以他笑了，好讓我放鬆警惕
{\fscx70\fscy70}And so he was smiling
to throw me off-guard.{\r}

1260
02:17:54,148 --> 02:17:56,810
哦，對阿，鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, it's all right, anyway, Bob.{\r}

1261
02:17:58,686 --> 02:18:01,587
大家都認為，鮑勃相當具有戲劇天賦
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was widely felt that
Bob possessed some acting talent...{\r}

1262
02:18:01,756 --> 02:18:04,020
而查理則一點天分都沒有
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and Charley, not a jot.{\r}

1263
02:18:04,191 --> 02:18:07,126
這畫怎麼那麼多灰呀
{\fscx70\fscy70}That picture's awful dusty.{\r}

1264
02:18:07,928 --> 02:18:11,056
大家希望查理不要那麼垂頭喪氣，喃喃自語
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley was only expected
not to slouch or mutter...{\r}

1265
02:18:11,232 --> 02:18:15,896
不要把這種心情傳給觀眾
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and to transport his sicknesses
to the alley before letting them go.{\r}

1266
02:18:45,299 --> 02:18:47,164
就這樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}And that's...{\r}

1267
02:18:47,735 --> 02:18:50,397
我殺了傑西·詹姆斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}...how I killed Jesse James.{\r}

1268
02:18:53,874 --> 02:18:57,401
到了1883年3月，認得鮑勃·福特的人
{\fscx70\fscy70}By October of 1883, Bob Ford
could be identified correctly...{\r}

1269
02:18:57,578 --> 02:19:01,844
已經比認得美國總統的人多了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...by more citizens than could
the president of the United States.{\r}

1270
02:19:02,516 --> 02:19:07,249
年僅20歲，他已經非常出名，可以媲美
傑西犯了14年偷竊罪所累積出來的名氣
{\fscx70\fscy70}He was as renowned at 20 as Jesse was
after 14 years of grand larceny.{\r}

1271
02:19:07,421 --> 02:19:09,616
你不會勾引到我的
{\fscx70\fscy70}You won't get your hooks into me.{\r}

1272
02:19:10,157 --> 02:19:14,890
對了，這就對了，坐到你男朋友邊上，吉貝爾
{\fscx70\fscy70}That's right. That's right.
Sit next to your boyfriend. Jezebel.{\r}

1273
02:19:15,062 --> 02:19:17,155
查理變得越發的迷信
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley was increasingly superstitious...{\r}

1274
02:19:17,331 --> 02:19:20,027
越發相信占卜者的建議
{\fscx70\fscy70}...increasingly subject
to the advice of soothsayers...{\r}

1275
02:19:20,201 --> 02:19:24,228
占卜者聲稱能用煙斗和糊藥治癒他的悲傷
{\fscx70\fscy70}...who promised to cure his miseries
with pipe smoke and poultices.{\r}

1276
02:19:24,405 --> 02:19:27,670
你見吉普賽人見得太多了，查理
{\fscx70\fscy70}You been spending too much time
with Gypsies, Charley.{\r}

1277
02:19:33,381 --> 02:19:34,746
靠
{\fscx70\fscy70}Shit.{\r}

1278
02:19:39,086 --> 02:19:41,646
這照片怎麼那麼多灰
{\fscx70\fscy70}The picture's awful dusty.{\r}

1279
02:19:42,089 --> 02:19:45,923
查理對傑西的演繹方式發生了變化
{\fscx70\fscy70}Something began to change
in Charley's stage portrayal of Jesse.{\r}

1280
02:19:46,093 --> 02:19:48,618
他的步態顯得更嫻熟
{\fscx70\fscy70}His gait seemed more practiced.{\r}

1281
02:19:48,796 --> 02:19:52,095
聲音越發和那人相似，讓人毛骨悚然
{\fscx70\fscy70}His voice was spookily similar
to the man's.{\r}

1282
02:19:52,266 --> 02:19:54,666
他新加入了一些對話
{\fscx70\fscy70}His newly suggested dialogue
was analogous...{\r}

1283
02:19:54,835 --> 02:19:57,861
彷彿出自傑西的創造
{\fscx70\fscy70}...to a script Jesse might have originated.{\r}

1284
02:20:00,674 --> 02:20:03,108
他開始用蔑視的眼神注視他的弟弟
{\fscx70\fscy70}He began to look at his younger brother
with spite...{\r}

1285
02:20:03,277 --> 02:20:05,905
彷彿他疑心，在以後的演出裡
{\fscx70\fscy70}...as if he suspected that
in some future performance...{\r}

1286
02:20:06,080 --> 02:20:10,608
他將面對羅伯特·福特的真槍實彈
{\fscx70\fscy70}...he might present himself
to a live cartridge in Robert Ford's gun.{\r}

1287
02:20:11,952 --> 02:20:13,783
殺人犯！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Murderer!{\r}

1288
02:20:14,121 --> 02:20:15,850
雜種！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Cur!{\r}

1289
02:20:16,490 --> 02:20:18,253
懦夫！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Coward!{\r}

1290
02:20:21,796 --> 02:20:26,324
你想看我有多大的膽子是嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You wanna investigate my courage?
Do you?{\r}

1291
02:20:26,734 --> 02:20:30,500
來啊！來啊！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Find out! Find out!{\r}

1292
02:20:35,142 --> 02:20:37,007
沒人來
{\fscx70\fscy70}Nobody.{\r}

1293
02:20:51,592 --> 02:20:53,389
懦夫！
{\fscx70\fscy70}Coward!{\r}

1294
02:21:18,586 --> 02:21:24,149
據他自己估計
鮑勃謀殺了傑西·詹姆斯800多次
{\fscx70\fscy70}By his own approximation, Bob
assassinated Jesse James over 800 times.{\r}

1295
02:21:24,325 --> 02:21:28,091
他猜，歷史上沒有任何人
曾這樣頻繁，或如此公開地
{\fscx70\fscy70}He suspected no one in history
had ever so often or so publicly...{\r}

1296
02:21:28,262 --> 02:21:31,459
重演一次背叛的行為
{\fscx70\fscy70}...recapitulated an act of betrayal.{\r}

1297
02:21:36,670 --> 02:21:39,434
鮑勃經常挑戰對於懦夫的定義
{\fscx70\fscy70}Bob always challenged
the allegations of cowardice...{\r}

1298
02:21:39,607 --> 02:21:42,542
但查理似乎認同這些定義
{\fscx70\fscy70}...but Charley seemed
to agree with them.{\r}

1299
02:21:42,810 --> 02:21:46,576
他提起芝·詹姆斯太太的時候
把她說得像聖母一樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}He spoke of Mrs. Zee James
as certain priests might the Madonna...{\r}

1300
02:21:46,747 --> 02:21:49,841
還給她寫了許多發自肺腑的長信
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and composed long soul-describing letters
to her...{\r}

1301
02:21:50,017 --> 02:21:52,212
請求她的原諒
{\fscx70\fscy70}...begging her forgiveness...{\r}

1302
02:21:53,521 --> 02:21:56,115
但這些信從未寄出過
{\fscx70\fscy70}...none of which he mailed.{\r}

1303
02:22:23,984 --> 02:22:29,581
大家覺得，暗殺了傑西·詹姆斯的人
下場就該和查理·福特一樣
{\fscx70\fscy70}Charley Ford became all that his countrymen
wanted an assassin of Jesse James to be.{\r}

1304
02:22:33,861 --> 02:22:39,731
傑西·詹姆斯殺了很多人
{\fscx70\fscy70}Jesse James was a man
Who killed many men{\r}

1305
02:22:40,935 --> 02:22:45,372
他搶了格倫代爾火車
{\fscx70\fscy70}He robbed the Glendale train{\r}

1306
02:22:45,606 --> 02:22:51,442
他劫富濟貧
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he stole from the rich
And he gave to the poor{\r}

1307
02:22:51,679 --> 02:22:56,616
他身手敏捷，頭腦機靈
{\fscx70\fscy70}He had a hand
And a heart and a brain{\r}

1308
02:22:57,418 --> 02:23:02,913
傑西有個妻子，她會為他哀悼
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, Jesse had a wife
To mourn for his life{\r}

1309
02:23:03,090 --> 02:23:08,187
還有三個勇敢的兒女
{\fscx70\fscy70}Three children
They were brave{\r}

1310
02:23:08,362 --> 02:23:13,959
但那個骯髒的懦夫，射殺了霍華德先生
{\fscx70\fscy70}But that dirty little coward
Who shot Mr. Howard{\r}

1311
02:23:14,201 --> 02:23:19,264
讓傑西·詹姆斯進了棺材
{\fscx70\fscy70}Has laid Jesse James in his grave{\r}

1312
02:23:20,341 --> 02:23:25,335
羅伯特·福特，這骯髒的小懦夫
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was Robert Ford
That dirty little coward{\r}

1313
02:23:26,080 --> 02:23:30,483
我想知道他的感受
{\fscx70\fscy70}I wonder how does he feel{\r}

1314
02:23:30,651 --> 02:23:36,385
他吃傑西的飯，睡傑西的床
{\fscx70\fscy70}For he ate at Jesse's bread
And he slept in Jesse's bed{\r}

1315
02:23:36,557 --> 02:23:41,585
卻讓可憐的傑西進了棺材
{\fscx70\fscy70}And he laid poor Jesse in his grave{\r}

1316
02:23:42,062 --> 02:23:47,591
傑西有個妻子，她會為他哀悼
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, Jesse had a wife
To mourn for his life{\r}

1317
02:23:47,768 --> 02:23:52,671
還有三個勇敢的兒女
{\fscx70\fscy70}Three children
They were brave{\r}

1318
02:23:52,840 --> 02:23:58,472
但那個骯髒的懦夫，射殺了霍華德先生
{\fscx70\fscy70}But that dirty little coward
Who shot Mr. Howard{\r}

1319
02:23:58,646 --> 02:24:02,810
讓可憐的傑西進了棺材
{\fscx70\fscy70}Has laid poor Jesse in his grave{\r}

1320
02:24:14,361 --> 02:24:16,386
我就是羅伯特·福特
{\fscx70\fscy70}I'm Robert Ford.{\r}

1321
02:24:27,107 --> 02:24:30,838
是兩個孩子，不是三個
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was two children, not three.{\r}

1322
02:24:42,222 --> 02:24:43,553
嘿
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hey.{\r}

1323
02:24:44,458 --> 02:24:47,018
回家去，好嗎
{\fscx70\fscy70}You get yourself home, son, okay?{\r}

1324
02:24:47,728 --> 02:24:51,755
出去，滾出我的地方
{\fscx70\fscy70}Come on. Get out of here.
Get out of my place.{\r}

1325
02:25:23,530 --> 02:25:25,725
他生氣極了的時候
{\fscx70\fscy70}He thought, at his angriest...{\r}

1326
02:25:25,899 --> 02:25:29,665
會想去見傑西殺害的人的家屬
{\fscx70\fscy70}...about visiting the kin
of Jesse's slaughtered victims:{\r}

1327
02:25:31,638 --> 02:25:34,903
普拉茨堡的威廉太太
{\fscx70\fscy70}Mrs. William Westfall in Plattsburg...{\r}

1328
02:25:37,411 --> 02:25:40,505
克萊縣的崴墨一家
{\fscx70\fscy70}...the Wymore family in Clay County...{\r}

1329
02:25:45,652 --> 02:25:49,952
甚至是馬薩諸塞州北田的
約瑟夫·黑伍德的遺孀
{\fscx70\fscy70}...perhaps even Mrs. Joseph Heywood
in Northfield, Minnesota.{\r}

1330
02:25:53,026 --> 02:25:56,018
他想到這些人的家裡
告訴他們他叫羅伯特·詹姆斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}He would go to their homes
and give his name as Robert Ford...{\r}

1331
02:25:56,196 --> 02:25:59,165
告訴他們他殺了傑西·詹姆斯
{\fscx70\fscy70}...the man who killed Jesse James.{\r}

1332
02:26:00,601 --> 02:26:03,661
他想像他們會對他充滿感激之情
{\fscx70\fscy70}He imagined they would
be grateful to him.{\r}

1333
02:26:54,621 --> 02:26:59,615
他只對多萊西·伊凡思坦白道出了真相
{\fscx70\fscy70}It was only with Dorothy Evans
that Bob spoke revealingly or plainly...{\r}

1334
02:26:59,793 --> 02:27:04,230
告訴她一些他以前都不知道自己知道的事情
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and it was with her that he spoke of
things he didn't know he knew.{\r}

1335
02:27:25,886 --> 02:27:29,947
他告訴她，他對射殺和後事都沒有真實的記憶
{\fscx70\fscy70}He told her that he had no real memory
of the shooting and its aftermath.{\r}

1336
02:27:30,123 --> 02:27:33,991
他只記得，舉起了那把傑西給他的槍
{\fscx70\fscy70}He could remember lifting the gun
that Jesse had given him...{\r}

1337
02:27:34,728 --> 02:27:38,755
然後就到耶穌受難日了，他看到了葬禮安排
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and then it was Good Friday and he was
reading about the funeral proceedings...{\r}

1338
02:27:38,932 --> 02:27:41,457
彷彿事情已經過去了很久
{\fscx70\fscy70}...as if they'd happened a long time ago.{\r}

1339
02:27:43,036 --> 02:27:45,163
你為什麼殺了他？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Why did you kill him?{\r}

1340
02:27:49,476 --> 02:27:51,501
他要殺我
{\fscx70\fscy70}Well, he was gonna kill me.{\r}

1341
02:27:56,717 --> 02:27:59,948
那唯一的原因就是你害怕了？
{\fscx70\fscy70}So you were scared
and that's the only reason?{\r}

1342
02:28:02,689 --> 02:28:04,088
對
{\fscx70\fscy70}Yeah.{\r}

1343
02:28:04,558 --> 02:28:06,617
還有賞金
{\fscx70\fscy70}And the reward money.{\r}

1344
02:28:12,432 --> 02:28:15,230
你想我換個話題嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}Do you want me to change the subject?{\r}

1345
02:28:23,443 --> 02:28:25,775
你知道我曾經期待什麼嗎？
{\fscx70\fscy70}You know what I expected?{\r}

1346
02:28:26,813 --> 02:28:28,804
掌聲
{\fscx70\fscy70}Applause.{\r}

1347
02:28:31,385 --> 02:28:35,549
我那時候才20歲，我不知道別人會怎麼看
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was only 20 years old then.
I couldn't see how it would look to people.{\r}

1348
02:28:39,660 --> 02:28:42,322
事情竟變成這樣，我很吃驚
{\fscx70\fscy70}I was surprised by what happened.{\r}

1349
02:28:43,397 --> 02:28:45,365
他們沒有鼓掌
{\fscx70\fscy70}They didn't applaud.{\r}

1350
02:28:48,802 --> 02:28:50,667
他為自己的吹噓
{\fscx70\fscy70}He was ashamed of his boasting...{\r}

1351
02:28:50,837 --> 02:28:53,704
自己假裝的勇敢無畏而感到羞恥
{\fscx70\fscy70}...his pretensions of courage
and ruthlessness.{\r}

1352
02:28:54,007 --> 02:28:57,773
他為自己的冷血無情
{\fscx70\fscy70}He was sorry about his cold-bloodedness,
his dispassion...{\r}

1353
02:28:59,413 --> 02:29:03,816
為自己無法表達自己真實的感情而充滿愧疚
{\fscx70\fscy70}...his inability to express
what he now believed was the case:{\r}

1354
02:29:06,386 --> 02:29:09,412
他很後悔殺了傑西
{\fscx70\fscy70}That he truly regretted killing Jesse...{\r}

1355
02:29:10,190 --> 02:29:13,182
他非常想念他
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that he missed the man
as much as anybody...{\r}

1356
02:29:13,727 --> 02:29:16,855
他希望，他不是非要殺了傑西來保命
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and wished his murder
hadn't been necessary.{\r}

1357
02:29:36,316 --> 02:29:38,409
即使當他在自己的酒吧裡穿行
{\fscx70\fscy70}Even as he circulated his saloon...{\r}

1358
02:29:38,585 --> 02:29:42,351
他也知道他走過之後，這些人的笑容就會消失
{\fscx70\fscy70}...he knew that the smiles disappeared
when he passed by.{\r}

1359
02:29:43,457 --> 02:29:45,288
他收到很多很多惡意信件
{\fscx70\fscy70}He received so many menacing letters...{\r}

1360
02:29:45,459 --> 02:29:48,895
到最後他讀的時候除了好奇，就沒有別的反應了
{\fscx70\fscy70}...that he could read them
without any reaction except curiosity.{\r}

1361
02:29:52,699 --> 02:29:57,500
他整天呆在屋裡，翻著撲克牌
{\fscx70\fscy70}He kept to his apartment all day,
flipping over playing cards...{\r}

1362
02:29:59,006 --> 02:30:03,500
在每張K和J牌裡注視自己的命運
{\fscx70\fscy70}...looking at his destiny
in every king and jack.{\r}

1363
02:30:07,714 --> 02:30:12,014
8號下午1點，愛德華·奧凱利來了
{\fscx70\fscy70}Edward O'Kelly came up from Bachelor
at 1 p.m. On the 8th.{\r}

1364
02:30:13,487 --> 02:30:17,423
他沒有什麼大計，沒有策略
{\fscx70\fscy70}He had no grand scheme, no strategy...{\r}

1365
02:30:17,591 --> 02:30:19,991
沒有和警方訂任何協議
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no agreement with higher authorities...{\r}

1366
02:30:20,160 --> 02:30:22,924
心裡只是暗暗期待著榮譽
{\fscx70\fscy70}...nothing beyond
a vague longing for glory...{\r}

1367
02:30:23,997 --> 02:30:28,263
和向羅伯特·福特報復的心情
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and a generalized wish
for revenge against Robert Ford.{\r}

1368
02:30:36,043 --> 02:30:39,308
- 昨晚怎樣？
- 不壞
{\fscx70\fscy70}- How'd it go last night?
- Not so bad.{\r}

1369
02:30:42,549 --> 02:30:43,948
另一支
{\fscx70\fscy70}The other one.{\r}

1370
02:30:46,453 --> 02:30:49,217
愛德華·奧凱利將因二級謀殺
{\fscx70\fscy70}Edward O'Kelly would be ordered
to serve a life sentence...{\r}

1371
02:30:49,389 --> 02:30:52,290
在科羅拉多懲戒所被判終身監禁
{\fscx70\fscy70}...in the Colorado Penitentiary
for second-degree murder.{\r}

1372
02:30:52,459 --> 02:30:55,223
最終，超過7000人簽名
{\fscx70\fscy70}Over 7000 signatures
would eventually be gathered...{\r}

1373
02:30:55,395 --> 02:30:57,659
請求釋放奧凱利
{\fscx70\fscy70}...on a petition asking for
O'Kelly's release...{\r}

1374
02:30:57,831 --> 02:31:02,825
1902年，州長詹姆斯·B·奧曼將其釋放
{\fscx70\fscy70}...and in 1902, Governor James B. Orman
would pardon the man.{\r}

1375
02:31:03,437 --> 02:31:07,840
你不應該戴那個領帶夾的，蛋白石不吉祥
{\fscx70\fscy70}You shouldn't be wearing that stickpin
again there, Bob. Opals are unlucky.{\r}

1376
02:31:09,276 --> 02:31:13,474
我運氣本身也不好
蛋白石可能還能給我轉運呢
{\fscx70\fscy70}My luck's not very good as it is. I don't
think an opal's gonna change that much.{\r}

1377
02:31:14,414 --> 02:31:15,847
我聽到了
{\fscx70\fscy70}I hear you.{\r}

1378
02:31:29,429 --> 02:31:31,294
沒有人會給鮑勃念頌詞
{\fscx70\fscy70}There would be no eulogies for Bob...{\r}

1379
02:31:32,999 --> 02:31:37,095
雜貨店也不會賣他遺體的照片
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no photographs of his body
would be sold in sundries stores...{\r}

1380
02:31:37,804 --> 02:31:42,173
沒有人會在雨天涌到街上去看他的葬禮行列
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no people would crowd the streets
in the rain to see his funeral cortege...{\r}

1381
02:31:43,910 --> 02:31:46,879
沒人會給他寫傳記
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no biographies would be written
about him...{\r}

1382
02:31:47,047 --> 02:31:49,607
沒有人會給孩子起他的名字
{\fscx70\fscy70}...no children named after him.{\r}

1383
02:31:51,184 --> 02:31:55,917
沒有人會付25美分去看他長大的那個屋子
{\fscx70\fscy70}No one would ever pay 25 cents
to stand in the rooms he grew up in.{\r}

1384
02:32:00,460 --> 02:32:02,189
你好啊，鮑勃
{\fscx70\fscy70}Hello, Bob.{\r}

1385
02:32:03,630 --> 02:32:07,828
槍聲響起，艾拉·梅會尖叫
{\fscx70\fscy70}The shotgun would ignite,
and Ella Mae would scream...{\r}

1386
02:32:08,635 --> 02:32:12,298
但羅伯特·福特只會躺在地板上
盯著天花板
{\fscx70\fscy70}...but Robert Ford would only lay
on the floor and look at the ceiling...{\r}

1387
02:32:12,472 --> 02:32:14,963
他的眼睛逐漸失去光彩
{\fscx70\fscy70}...the light going out of his eyes...{\r}

1388
02:32:15,142 --> 02:32:17,872
他沒想到該說什麼話
{\fscx70\fscy70}...before he could find the right words.{\r}

